The `ORDER BY` clause sorts the result set. By default (or with `ASC`), it sorts in ascending order. Example:
```sql
SELECT * FROM TableName ORDER BY AttributeName;
-- or explicitly:
SELECT * FROM TableName ORDER BY AttributeName ASC;
```

